%T A397118 537129600,3047909792,17295329355,98141764557,556903143800,
%U A397118 3160131229122,17932082608935,101755119407447,577406728585500,3276479059477152,18592293226621415,105501472300607037,598665294360619500
%N A397118 Size of clusters of star triples of Family D in the Spectre aperiodic monotile tiling.
%C A397118 The chiral aperiodic Spectre monotile tiling (discovered in 2023) forms hierarchical, fractal macro-structures called clusters of star triples (three Spectre tiles head-on) of five different families, megastars of two types, and palindromes of megastars. This sequence represents the total number of star triples in successive generations of Family D clusters. The fractal growth is governed by the limiting constant 5.674473356937... = 1 + 2*sqrt(6) * cos((1/3) * arccos(sqrt(6)/4)), which is the largest root of the cubic equation x^3 - 3*x^2 - 15*x - 1 = 0.
%C A397118 The sequence exhibits a strict periodic behavior in modulo 10 arithmetic (the last digits form a repeating cycle of 2, 5, 7, 0). Furthermore, due to the algebraic cancellation of the tens digits (3*(-10) + 15*(-20) + 1*(+30) = -300 == 0 mod 100), every 4th term is exactly divisible by 100, ending in 00.
%H A397118 Boris K. Horvat, <a href="/A397118/b397118.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..100</a>
%H A397118 Boris K. Horvat, <a href="https://zenodo.org/records/18421797">Anatomy of the Spectre Tiling</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%H A397118 David Smith, J. S. Myers, C. S. Kaplan, and C. Goodman-Strauss, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.17743">A chiral aperiodic monotile</a>, arXiv:2305.17743 [math.CO], 2023-2024.
%H A397118 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (4,12,-14,-1).
%F A397118 a(n) = 3*a(n-1) + 15*a(n-2) + a(n-3) + 12 (for n>3, where a(1)=2, a(2)=15, a(3)=87).
%F A397118 a(n) = 4*a(n-1) + 12*a(n-2) - 14*a(n-3) - a(n-4) (for n>3, where a(0)=0, a(1)=2, a(2)=15, a(3)=87).
%F A397118 a(n) = a(n-1) + A397120(n) + A397121(n) + A397122(n-1) (for n>0, with a(0)=0, A397122(0)=0).
%F A397118 a(n) = A397117(n) + A397121(n) (for n>0).
%F A397118 a(4*n) == 0 (mod 100).
%F A397118 a(n) = c_1*r_1^n + c_2*r_2^n + c_3*r_3^n - 2/3, where r_1, r_2, r_3 are the roots of x^3 - 3*x^2 - 15*x - 1 = 0.
%F A397118 G.f.: x*(2 + x)*(1 + 3*x)/((1 - x)*(1 - 3*x - 15*x^2 - x^3)). - _Stefano Spezia_, Jun 27 2026
%e A397118 For n = 2, the cluster of Family D has a(2) = 15 star triples. It is formed by the previous generation's cluster a(1) = 2 and is inflated/extended by one palindrome of all Type A megastars up to generation 1, PA(1) = 2, by a Type A megastar of size MA(2) = 4, and by a Type C megastar of size MC(2) = 7, giving 2 + 2 + 4 + 7 = 15 star triples.
%e A397118 For n = 3, the cluster of Family D has a(3) = 87 star triples. It is formed by the previous generation's cluster a(2) = 15 and is inflated/extended by one palindrome of all Type A megastars up to generation 2, PA(2) = 10, by a Type A megastar of size MA(3) = 25, and by a Type C megastar of size MC(3) = 37,giving 15 + 10 + 25 + 37 = 87 star triples.
%t A397118 LinearRecurrence[{4, 12, -14, -1}, {2, 15, 87, 500}, 24] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 27 2026 *)
%Y A397118 Cf. A397115 (Family A), A397116 (Family C), A397117 (Family B), A397119 (Family E), A397120 (Megastar A), A397121 (Megastar C), A397122 (Palindrom A), A397123 (Sequence A).
